Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.60,0:00:04.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With just three days remaining before the serial murder case expired...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.31,0:00:10.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A criminal psychologist by the name of Hiramune\NDouji{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} repeatedly provoked the serial killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.40,0:00:11.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And was later found murdered at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.95,0:00:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On his back was...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.16,0:00:16.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A wound in the form of a Z.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.99,0:00:20.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the bodies of the serial killer's three previous victims...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.95,0:00:24.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were the letters E S W in that order.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.62,0:00:27.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Haibara and Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} saw someone suspicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.50,0:00:29.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And mentioned that he had been whistling...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.71,0:00:33.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police concluded the serial killer had struck again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.84,0:00:37.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to visit the bereaved families of the victims...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.68,0:00:40.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We accompanied Detective Takagi as he interviewed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.06,0:00:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was then that we discovered that the\Nconnection between the four victims...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.39,0:00:44.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was actually just mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.90,0:00:48.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The serial murderer...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.65,0:00:51.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll uncover your true face without a doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.65,0:00:55.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love is eternal, labyrinths are mysterious.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.61,0:00:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saturday nights are for mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.95,0:00:59.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi has enthusiastically gone into a pitfall!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.08,0:01:01.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An emergency development of love and mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.16,0:01:03.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.75,0:01:05.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.50,0:01:07.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.44,0:02:57.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I do recognize these gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.15,0:03:02.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were frequent customers that would\Nalways share a table, quite a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.91,0:03:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brings back memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.08,0:03:08.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.37,0:03:10.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the criminal psychologist, Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.21,0:03:13.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This picture is from twenty years later, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.09,0:03:18.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This must be the student that would always play with those three.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.55,0:03:21.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you're saying those four did play mahjong here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.59,0:03:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every Saturday night at 10:00 PM, always these four.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.64,0:03:27.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was the doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.77,0:03:29.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The associate professor of science and engineering...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.68,0:03:30.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The beginning lawyer...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.98,0:03:33.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the criminal psychology university student.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.36,0:03:36.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a gap in their ages, but they had things in common.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.98,0:03:41.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They would often discuss and reason\Nthrough cases over games of mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.40,0:03:45.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The culprit was the husband that was interviewed."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.45,0:03:47.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The trick utilized his expert medical knowledge."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.33,0:03:51.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The crazy thing was that they were usually right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.08,0:03:52.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.79,0:03:54.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you asking about them?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.75,0:03:56.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.71,0:03:58.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, by the same criminal...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.55,0:04:00.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'd you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.51,0:04:02.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All four at once!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.55,0:04:05.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the first was twenty years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.76,0:04:06.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't know about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.22,0:04:09.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I haven't kept an eye on the news for a long time...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.89,0:04:13.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only checked the cases that those four mentioned in the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.77,0:04:17.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I only bought the paper for those two years they were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.23,0:04:21.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When they stopped coming, I no longer bought them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.28,0:04:22.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stopped coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.78,0:04:23.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.78,0:04:28.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't hear it very well, but they mentioned a "complete crime."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.45,0:04:32.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, the student was the only one who would come.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.12,0:04:37.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would sit down at a table alone and polish tiles all by his lonesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.30,0:04:42.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they were killed, the culprit was likely that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.05,0:04:44.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying you have a lead!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.88,0:04:49.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a customer that was always\Nannoyed at the deductions of those four.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.22,0:04:54.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After everyone else stopped coming, that one man\Nwould always tease the lonesome student...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.81,0:04:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It even resulted in a big fight between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.32,0:05:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remember him yelling at one point...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.82,0:05:04.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm gonna do something about all of you!"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.65,0:05:06.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And could you please tell us who that was?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.82,0:05:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.95,0:05:10.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had a reputation as being bad, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.41,0:05:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for his name...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.12,0:05:15.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, there was that incident where that gun disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.96,0:05:18.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When a police officer left his police box open...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.50,0:05:21.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His handgun ended up disappearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.50,0:05:24.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though it caused quite a stir,\Nit was returned within two days.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.72,0:05:28.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were rumors that that customer was responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.01,0:05:31.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And back during their fight, this case of tiles was scattered about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.14,0:05:35.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Due to the damage, they couldn't be used anymore, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.35,0:05:39.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And those mahjong tiles were thrown by that customer as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.36,0:05:41.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.32,0:05:43.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who cleaned up the tiles?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.19,0:05:45.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.32,0:05:51.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the police came to stop the fight and took those two\Naway, I picked them up and collected them all in this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.87,0:05:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you're saying that the only fingerprints on those tiles...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.79,0:05:56.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Belong to you, Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.96,0:06:00.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that one other customer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.04,0:06:02.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is this boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.92,0:06:05.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's just observing for a social studies class...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.51,0:06:08.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention, if those two were hauled in by the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.09,0:06:10.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There should still be records of it somewhere, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.09,0:06:11.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.76,0:06:12.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.31,0:06:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll take these damaged mahjong tiles along with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.52,0:06:19.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And your fingerprints as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.40,0:06:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, now that you mention it, I got a weird call last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.15,0:06:32.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A guy asked if a doctor, an associate professor, a lawyer,\Nand a criminal psychology student all used to play here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.62,0:06:34.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.79,0:06:37.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've found a lead to the suspect in the serial killer case?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.91,0:06:38.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.71,0:06:43.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Twenty years ago, the suspect got in an argument with\NHiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and was restrained in a police box!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.42,0:06:45.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Address and occupation unknown...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.51,0:06:47.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.84,0:06:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kibo Dokurou!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.47,0:06:50.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kibo...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.84,0:06:52.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you say Kibo Dokurou!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.51,0:06:53.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Kibo"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.47,0:06:54.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean that burglar-murderer?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.93,0:07:01.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm fairly certain he was just discharged from prison a\Nfew days ago after a fifteen year prison stint, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.27,0:07:02.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.19,0:07:04.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason the serial murders stopped during those fifteen years...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.44,0:07:08.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was incarcerated for that period and was unable to continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.07,0:07:09.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.78,0:07:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's probable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.07,0:07:11.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.41,0:07:14.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We must find this man at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.74,0:07:16.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bring him before me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.45,0:07:17.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.12,0:07:21.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he's really enthusiastic about this case...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.17,0:07:22.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.46,0:07:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he found a woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.08,0:07:24.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.17,0:07:27.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've heard some occasional rumors to that effect...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.63,0:07:29.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be sure that he's on his guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.13,0:07:32.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you see it in movies and dramas?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.89,0:07:36.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'll make a careful promise to his wife or lover...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.35,0:07:40.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then end up taking a bullet of misfortune\Nfrom a suspect, dying in the line of duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.44,0:07:44.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, those—they're just stories, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.56,0:07:46.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Morimura fell victim to it as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.19,0:07:50.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had planned to marry the very next month...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.45,0:07:54.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, to impress the woman, he acted on a whim of haste...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.45,0:07:57.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And was run over by the suspect's car.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.95,0:07:59.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.75,0:08:00.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're going!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.54,0:08:05.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Age has brought my time on as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.42,0:08:07.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This scar...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.34,0:08:11.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It reacted when I heard someone had met the suspect in a sauna.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.01,0:08:17.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there was even more pain when I walked\Ninto the crime scene of the fourth victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.01,0:08:22.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, with only a few hours behind us,\Nit's as if it has all come to an end...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.18,0:08:23.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the pain is long gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.56,0:08:30.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could be heaven signaling to me, saying that my work here is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.24,0:08:33.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.65,0:08:36.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just thinking you had investigated quickly, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.49,0:08:38.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was helping from the shadows, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.33,0:08:40.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.04,0:08:42.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that means the hot springs trip is off, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.96,0:08:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.87,0:08:46.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go with him to the hot springs!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.83,0:08:49.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He still found the culprit, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.04,0:08:50.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be so narrow-minded!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.71,0:08:51.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I cannot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.76,0:08:53.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Personal feelings are not permitted in investigations!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.88,0:08:54.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had almost forgot...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.30,0:08:58.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just one mistake in this line of work can mean death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.60,0:09:03.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll take these kids home in my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.85,0:09:06.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You go accompany Chiba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and the others in the search for Kibo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.35,0:09:07.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.36,0:09:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Sato speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.03,0:09:16.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We already got Kibo!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.49,0:09:20.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he was found in his apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.24,0:09:22.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He decided to come along voluntarily...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.87,0:09:26.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we need to get the son of the first\Nvictim Nabei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.79,0:09:28.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's to identify his voice, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.92,0:09:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He heard the voice of the suspect as a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.21,0:09:33.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.05,0:09:33.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll leave it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.38,0:09:37.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you get Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.43,0:09:38.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.64,0:09:43.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe he was captured so easily, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.27,0:09:44.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The serial killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.06,0:09:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought we would be out on an exciting chase after him...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.73,0:09:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At least a gun fight, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.19,0:09:53.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You only see that in movies and dramas!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.40,0:09:54.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In reality, it's pretty plain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.65,0:09:56.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're looking bleak.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.24,0:10:01.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Z on Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s back is what's bothering me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.12,0:10:04.45,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,As for as the three previous victims...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.49,0:10:06.04,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Their bodies had...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.04,0:10:09.04,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,E S W carved into them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.21,0:10:11.08,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The last letter should be N, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.59,0:10:14.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that there was no pattern at all, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.38,0:10:21.35,Signs,,0,0,0,,Touzai (East/West)\NNanboku (South/North)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.38,0:10:17.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's Touzai Nanboku...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.01,0:10:19.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It shouldn't be E S W N...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.18,0:10:21.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But instead E W S N.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.68,0:10:22.43,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.55,0:10:25.81,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,If it were mahjong, ton nan shaa pei would work, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.89,0:10:28.73,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,All we can cover right now E S W.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.10,0:10:30.85,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Why would the last letter be a Z?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.36,0:10:34.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer could have just planned to\Nposition the body sideways, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.94,0:10:37.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you rotate a Z, you get an N.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.03,0:10:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if that's so, it makes you wonder\Nwhy he didn't leave it sideways, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.41,0:10:43.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.74,0:10:45.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another point of concern...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.58,0:10:48.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would be the Ctrl key being covered with Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.91,0:10:51.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is, the control key, along with the C key.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.13,0:10:55.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though pressing those two keys results in the copy function...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.96,0:10:58.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would he need to grasp onto the mouse cord?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.76,0:11:00.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Mouse"?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.18,0:11:03.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to operate a PC, you need to\Nhave that round device plugged in, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.26,0:11:07.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cord running from it resembles a mouse tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.35,0:11:08.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why it's known as a mouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.19,0:11:11.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.48,0:11:14.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he caught the tail of a mouse...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.27,0:11:15.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person must be a cat, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.23,0:11:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, you don't have to say it in such a cute way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.90,0:11:20.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.66,0:11:23.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.91,0:11:26.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no need to be laughing about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.87,0:11:27.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.08,0:11:29.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.16,0:11:30.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's how it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.12,0:11:33.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The serial murders came to an end...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.33,0:11:35.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fifteen years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.75,0:11:39.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You gotta help me here, Officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.26,0:11:43.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been behind bars for fifteen years and just now finally got out...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.51,0:11:46.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have no desire to kill anyone again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.93,0:11:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think this is our man?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.60,0:11:52.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the one who heard the suspect's\Nvoice back then was Nabei Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.27,0:11:55.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should wait until he can confirm it for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.23,0:11:58.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Megure...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.61,0:11:59.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would you handle it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.44,0:12:06.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the officer that put a big scar on your\Nback long ago appeared in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.74,0:12:08.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd be surprised...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.08,0:12:11.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When that guy passed by me just a minute ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.41,0:12:13.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't even raise an eyebrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.79,0:12:17.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that this Kibo Dokurou...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.34,0:12:20.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kibo Dokurou...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.42,0:12:21.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't the serial killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.72,0:12:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.80,0:12:27.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the victim today was that criminal psychologist, Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.22,0:12:29.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's likely that he was acquainted with the real suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.06,0:12:33.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, since those two had been involved in a fight long ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.89,0:12:37.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't imagine they would agree to meet in that room together.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.98,0:12:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.86,0:12:41.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left a dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.28,0:12:45.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A message that said his killer was not actually the serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.99,0:12:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the blood on the Ctrl and C keys, he meant "copy."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.83,0:12:52.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And by holding onto the mouse cord...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.58,0:12:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was referring to the cat holding the mouse's tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.67,0:12:56.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we combine them...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.63,0:12:58.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Copycat."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.79,0:13:03.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the one who killed him trying to\Nbe the serial killer was just that—an imitator.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.63,0:13:19.48,Signs,,0,0,0,,mouhou han
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.63,0:13:05.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An imitator!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.80,0:13:07.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.18,0:13:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it like mixed boiled rice?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.22,0:13:14.48,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,100)}maze gohan
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.10,0:13:12.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like a blue birthmark on a baby's bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.56,0:13:13.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not an imitator.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.02,0:13:16.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What they mean by imitator...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.98,0:13:19.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is an offender that copies another criminal's methods.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.61,0:13:23.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why is it a cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.94,0:13:27.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's simply because a kitten always tries to imitate the mother cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.16,0:13:31.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} know that it was an imitator?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.04,0:13:33.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's simply because...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.37,0:13:37.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murdered Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.42,0:13:39.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Happens to be the original serial killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.79,0:13:45.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you consider that, it makes perfect sense\Nas to why a Z was carved into his back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.97,0:13:53.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Due to Superintendent Matsumoto, the serial killer\Nhad a big 1-shaped scar on his back from a katana.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.47,0:13:56.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To cover that scar...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.35,0:14:00.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to not let anyone discover that Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the serial killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.56,0:14:04.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had to come up with a letter of the alphabet that would fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.28,0:14:05.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.94,0:14:10.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By doing this, he is able to camouflage the murder\Nas one committed by the serial killer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.03,0:14:16.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If all went well, the police would continue\Nchasing an already deceased serial killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.21,0:14:20.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While the real murderer would never be suspected.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.54,0:14:21.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.38,0:14:22.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which one is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.38,0:14:23.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That copycat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.25,0:14:26.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since they knew about the whistling habit...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.47,0:14:29.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was someone close to one of the victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.31,0:14:36.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.73,0:14:38.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even the light is still on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.44,0:14:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's open...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.77,0:14:42.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nabei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.11,0:14:46.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the police officer that was here earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.07,0:14:48.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nabei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.11,0:14:49.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you come to the station with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.53,0:14:51.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nabei{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.29,0:15:04.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of the victims' family members knew about\Nthe letters being cut into the bodies, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.50,0:15:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for those that knew about the whistling and mahjong references...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.93,0:15:12.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.68,0:15:14.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.68,0:15:18.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the one who heard the crime in\Nhis house as a child, Nabei Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.52,0:15:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.39,0:15:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also knew the voice of the criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.56,0:15:26.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's likely that he heard the voice and tone of\NHiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on TV, and remembered it by chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.11,0:15:29.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That made him go searching for the\Nmahjong parlor his father had visited...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.24,0:15:33.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which is how he found out how the other\Nthree had been connected to Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.82,0:15:38.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, he was convinced Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the serial murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.91,0:15:42.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it took him fifteen years to come to that conclusion...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.42,0:15:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That could mean Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did not become familiar\Nwith mahjong terminology until adulthood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.13,0:15:48.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.55,0:15:52.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This Eiki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is the really angry person we went to visit earlier, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.59,0:15:54.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person—just now, Detective Takagi went to...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.72,0:16:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're the cop they've got looking into the serial murder case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.52,0:16:05.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like you brought a gun along, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.61,0:16:09.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess the reason you came alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.99,0:16:12.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is because no one realized I was the culprit, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.03,0:16:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "culprit"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.16,0:16:16.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.07,0:16:18.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be that you killed your father fifteen years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.04,0:16:20.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.87,0:16:22.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was all Hiramune's doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.58,0:16:26.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just taking out vengeance for my father today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.96,0:16:28.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I called that bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.42,0:16:30.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I just remembered something about my father's murder."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.55,0:16:34.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I wanted to run it by a criminal psychologist\Nsuch as yourself before going to the police."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.34,0:16:37.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right over the phone, the meeting was set.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.97,0:16:40.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He never expected I was coming for revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.35,0:16:45.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With just a little convincing, he felt like talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The motive for murdering my father was apparently\Nthe "complete crime" that came up during mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.57,0:16:55.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something about whether it would be possible to steal\Na gun from the police without anyone taking notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.70,0:16:58.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They had differing opinions, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.37,0:17:03.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune decided to prove to them he\Ncould really pull off a complete crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.41,0:17:12.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He expected them to praise him, but instead, the doctor\Nand professor said that the crime stops at mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.63,0:17:16.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He grew afraid that they would reveal the truth and\Nruin his future, so he did something about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.09,0:17:22.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My father stayed quiet, since he knew it was his\Njoking around that encouraged him to try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.89,0:17:24.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some five years later...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.23,0:17:31.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My father suggested that they turn themselves into\Nthe police, so his mouth had to be silenced as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.44,0:17:33.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.53,0:17:34.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What should we do here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.20,0:17:38.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if we take off in your patrol car, they'll get me sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.45,0:17:43.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.41,0:17:44.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My cellphone...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.20,0:17:45.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lookie here...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.21,0:17:46.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this a call from your girlfriend, Cop?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.33,0:17:48.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Terrific.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.42,0:17:49.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have her come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.75,0:17:51.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She can be my hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.54,0:17:53.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, don't you worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.59,0:17:57.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I do manage to get away, I'll set her free.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.93,0:18:00.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, hurry and answer it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.35,0:18:02.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not that I need to tell you, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.43,0:18:04.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you say anything fishy, I'll use the gun and...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.06,0:18:07.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.94,0:18:09.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems I broke my cellphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.52,0:18:13.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When it comes to hostages, I guess it'll just be me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.98,0:18:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.78,0:18:18.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.61,0:18:20.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is Nabei Eiki?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.41,0:18:21.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.28,0:18:24.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If nothing else, he's at least responsible for killing Hiramune{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.37,0:18:29.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi was en route to pick him up, but I can't seem to contact him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.29,0:18:31.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and send back-up, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.09,0:18:34.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is to all investigators!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.88,0:18:36.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Move to the house of Nabei Eiki immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.88,0:18:40.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's highly likely he is now in possession of Takagi's handgun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.84,0:18:43.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take absolute caution there's little time!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.22,0:18:45.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.10,0:18:47.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Any minute could cost our man his life!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.06,0:18:50.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.61,0:18:56.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Son of a bitch...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.78,0:18:59.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do I look like a moron to you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.79,0:19:07.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.25,0:19:09.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're done for!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.50,0:19:12.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it, they must have...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.54,0:19:14.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Figured it all out!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.04,0:19:15.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.92,0:19:16.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.51,0:19:19.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No choice...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.51,0:19:21.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I rush him now...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.85,0:19:31.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.81,0:19:34.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.98,0:19:35.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.61,0:19:37.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shot...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.53,0:19:45.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.45,0:19:46.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.62,0:19:49.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a common pattern in movies and dramas.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.37,0:19:51.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.04,0:19:54.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just because of the hot springs promise...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.46,0:19:56.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} have to die for it!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.25,0:19:58.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hot springs?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.05,0:20:00.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.34,0:20:01.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.76,0:20:03.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all right, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.13,0:20:06.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He happened to put this material evidence in his chest pocket...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.01,0:20:09.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, following the pattern, the criminal's bullet landed there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.27,0:20:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That mahjong tile...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.89,0:20:13.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.31,0:20:16.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He put it in his chest pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.32,0:20:22.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} rushing at Nabei Eiki and getting shot...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.45,0:20:25.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of the other officers came out just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.70,0:20:30.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of him, this case only had one victim in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.70,0:20:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.79,0:20:35.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since they finished treatment, he's been in the ward...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.88,0:20:38.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sound asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.54,0:22:02.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that song he was whistling...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.59,0:22:06.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The author had written, "This is how it has\Nto be," which had always reminded him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.80,0:22:10.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, in order to remember those Saturday night deduction battles...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.85,0:22:17.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiramune Douji would reminisce while whistling that tune.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.10,0:22:18.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what Superintendent Matsumoto said.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.15,0:22:20.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.81,0:22:21.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, oh well...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.32,0:22:25.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you're injured, I guess we have to cancel the hot springs trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.49,0:22:29.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you mean the deal was still valid!?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.28,0:22:29.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.53,0:22:32.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looked like you really gave it your all, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.91,0:22:34.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.58,0:22:35.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's too bad, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.95,0:22:39.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It always ends like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.25,0:22:39.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.92,0:22:43.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The time during the bombing case...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.34,0:22:46.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the time during the Hammer Man case...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.51,0:22:49.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's always so close...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.97,0:22:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which room is Takagi's?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.52,0:22:57.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe it's 304.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.77,0:22:59.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hot springs...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.94,0:23:00.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hot springs?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.23,0:23:04.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what do you mean by "so close"?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.15,0:23:05.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.32,0:23:08.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just interruptions...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.20,0:23:11.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.91,0:23:12.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.83,0:23:16.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi just took his medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.99,0:23:18.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's fast asleep in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.83,0:23:20.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why it's best...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.67,0:23:22.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To not wake him!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.25,0:23:23.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You would like him to recover, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.25,0:23:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.63,0:23:27.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess we can come back later, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.09,0:23:28.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.32,0:23:54.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'll definitely take us to the hot springs with them now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.66,0:23:55.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Definitely!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.20,0:23:58.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I don't think that's likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.16,0:24:02.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean that spooky house?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.08,0:24:05.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently there's some strange guy living in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.75,0:24:09.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems we need to scout out that house, like the police would.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.96,0:24:11.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, we are the Detective Boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.43,0:24:15.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what about the nameplate on the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.93,0:24:17.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, that person...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.18,0:24:20.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would they move into such a spooky house?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.31,0:24:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.27,0:24:24.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every mystery deserves to be solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.58,0:24:48.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.42,0:24:49.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nameplate
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.17,0:24:51.46,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The nameplate at my house says "Yoshida"!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.51,0:24:52.38,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What about you, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.38,0:24:53.67,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Ah, I guess it's Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.67,0:24:55.68,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He's a freeloader.
